question: What are genes related to Ablepharon-macrostomia syndrome?
agent_answer: The gene associated with Ablepharon-macrostomia syndrome is TWIST2. This association is considered causal for the syndrome. For more information, you can visit the [Monarch Initiative gene page for TWIST2](https://monarchinitiative.org/gene/HGNC:20670).
